That summer feeling 🌞🎶 of eating Flavor Punch Plum + Campari Semifreddo and Pickled Green Plum Salad al fresco for episode 2 of ‘Sweet + Savory’ 

🍑🍑🍑

Sweet + Savory - PLUMS!!! For the sweet, I made a flavor punch plum + Campari semifreddo, my favorite frozen dessert that can be made at home without any fancy equipment. The sour cream gives it a nice tang while the Campari imbues a welcome bitterness that will keep you coming back bite after bite.

I’ve been making versions of this salad meets antipasto plate all summer but wanted to try pickling the plums for an extra vinegary kick that somehow made the plums even more succulent. I made a pesto vinaigrette using @pineapplecollaborative x @marthastoumen’s rose vinegar and topped everything off with @chloecooks___ pistachio dukkah. 

So are you sweet or savory? Recipes coming soon…

On Eclipsing 🌙 This eclipse cracked me open in a very un-chill way. Even though these are energetics I’m usually used to navigating - self reflection, intention, grounding - it felt like I was being forced to release core parts of what I’ve built my identity around with no clear path forward. Like a very raw factory reset that even my double Capricorn ethos couldn’t explain away. 

Transformation is always applauded, but what about the mourning that it takes to get there? Who can hold space when it’s not a mirror you want to be reflected? When it’s not a rock bottom or a rut but a secret third thing? 

So in an attempt to get off my phone and out of my head I went to the hot springs the morning of the eclipse. To sweat out the uncertainty and soak in the pools that felt like they were filled with all the sulfurous tears I’d been crying. It was nice to be held by the earth among the ruins of an abandoned resort from the 1800s. How many other women have come here seeking the same solace? 

Maybe by the lunar eclipse on the 28th a clearer picture will emerge.. maybe not. Trying to hold onto patience and trust in the meantime and that sometimes you have to close your eyes to see the truth 🐚

24 hours in Big Sur - if you’re starting from the south, make your first stop in Los Olivos for a coffee/quick breakfast @matteistavernauberge 🤠 If you want to take your time exploring there’s lots of shops/wineries in the area or you can pop over to Solvang/Buellton/Los Alamos for food, thrifting, or some California kitsch. If it’s open I also recommend the Lompoc Mission for some history of the area.

Right now you have to drive through Carmel/Monterey to get to Big Sur and I recommend @altabakery (their blue corn cookie especially) then a walk around fishermen’s warf/the aquarium if you have time. When you enter Big Sur go where the wind takes you. Pull over at every vista, go to Nepenthe at sunset, and if you want to get as close to the sea take a walk down to Partington Cove. 

@deetjensbigsurinn is my favorite place in the world to stay, and right now they’re running a very generous winter discount during the week. Befriend the property cats, hike to the bench at sunrise, meditate in the redwoods, and their restaurant is always so comforting (the blueberry pancakes for breakfast are a classic!) don’t leave without a meal @bigsurbakery and stopping at the @henrymillerlib 🌊

On your way out, take a walk around Carmel for the storybook architecture and a peak @marie_clare_ ‘s folk art murals @hofsashouse and around town 🌞You’ll never regret a pit stop @madonnainn1958 but this time I kept it more low key and found an incredible Japanese spot, Goshi sushi, inside the Creamery food hall. The California coast is wild and secluded and there’s so much to be found either on a road trip with pals, lovers, or solo. 

I hope these snippets give you a taste of the peacefulness and awe I’m filled with that keeps bringing me back 🙏🏼
